==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: drip-dry
<hw>drip-dry</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>treated so as to be
easily or quickly washed and dried and requiring little or no ironing;
-- of clothing.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> wash-and-wear.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>requiring no ironing; -- used of fabrics and
clothing; <as>as, <ex>drip-dry</ex> shirts for travel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> permanent-press.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dripping</ent>⟦br⟧
